ced Scorecard is a strategic management technique developed by Kaplan and Norton that provides top management with an integrated set of performance measures from four perspectives: financial, customer, internal business processes, and learning and growth. This approach to performance management ensures that internal systems and processes support customer and financial objectives, encourages integration between departments, and allows for performance measurement and control actions. It is used to align business activities with the vision and strategy of the organization, improve internal and external communications, and monitor organizational performance against strategic goals. The Balanced Scorecard comprises an integrated framework of financial and non-financial performance measures that aim to clarify, communicate, and manage strategy implementation across the four perspectives.\",22\n1101,\"\"\"3ES\"\"\",\"\"\"The 3Es stand for economy, efficiency, and effectiveness, which are used to achieve Value for Money (VFM) in the public sector.\"\"\",1\n1098,\"\"\"LEADING AND LAGGING INDICATORS\"\"\",\"\"\"Leading indicators predict future performance, while lagging indicators reflect past performance. Both are used in the balanced scorecard to provide a comprehensive view of performance.\"\"\",1\n1099,\"\"\"CRITICAL SUCCESS FACTOR\"\"\",\"\"\"A performance outcome that an organisation requires to achieve success.\"\"\",1\n1112,\"\"\"KAPLAN AND NORTON\"\"\",\"\"\"Developers of the balanced scorecard approach, which integrates financial and non-financial performance measures.\"\"\",1\n1113,\"\"\"PERFORMANCE MEASURE\"\"\",\"\"\"A quantitative or qualitative characterisation of performance used to evaluate progress toward an objective.\"\"\",1\n1114,\"\"\"OBJECTIVE\"\"\",\"\"\"A specific, measurable statement of what will be done to achieve goals within a defined time frame.\"\"\",1\n1115,\"\"\"INITIATIVES\"\"\",\"\"\"Actions taken to improve performance in line with the ob